[2]
Date: Thu 14 Aug 2003
From: David Hutto <David_Hutto@BIOGEN.COM>

Similarity to transmissible venereal tumors in dogs
---------------------------------------------------
The description of a transmissible large round cell tumor is reminiscent of
transmissible venereal tumor (TVT) of dogs (other canids may be infected).
Notable differences to the described disease in Tasmanian devils is that
TVT is clearly transmitted venereally, often regresses spontaneously, and
has a somewhat different cytomorphology (high nuclear:cytoplasmic ratio).
It is the first neoplasm to have been shown to be transmissible, but a
specific etiology has not been demonstrated. Presumably it has been ruled
out in these Australian cases?
--
David L Hutto DVM, PhD, D-ACVP
Veterinary and Comparative Pathology
Biogen, Inc.
<David_Hutto@BIOGEN.COM>
See Also
Undiagnosed deaths, Tasmanian devils - Australia (02) 20030812.1999
